HEADWORD: Tripinnatifid
<hw>Tri`pin*nat"i*fid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>tri-</ets> + <ets>pinnatifid</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>Thrice pinnately cleft; -- said of a pinnatifid leaf when its
segments are pinnatifid, and the subdivisions of these also are
pinnatifid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tripitaka</ent>⟦br⟧
